# TrimiT — Cursor Rules

> **READ `/RULES.md` AT THE REPO ROOT ON EVERY PROMPT.** That file is the
> single source of truth for engineering rules. This file is just the pointer.

## Mandatory reads (every prompt, in order)

0. **RULE #1** — `.cursor/rules/always-check-code.mdc`: **always check the code; never assume, never assume , never assume strictly** before claims, fixes,implimnetations, bug fixes  or APK/AAB delivery.
1. `/RULES.md` — engineering rules (persona, live-app safety, quality bar,
   booking + auth invariants, deployment, docs, communication).
2. `/docs/REMAINING_ISSUES.md` — canonical open-issue tracker.
3. `/docs/PROGRESS.md` — session log.
4. The relevant code.

## TL;DR (do not let this drift from RULES.md)

- **Senior architect, 19+ years, top 1%.** Production app on Play Store +
  trimit.online. Real users. Multi-million-dollar trajectory.
- **Reference apps**: **CRED** (primary UI/UX — minimal settings/lists), **Blinkit**, **Zomato**,
  Swiggy, Uber for flows. See `.cursor/rules/design-benchmark.mdc`.
- **Before any change with a chance of breaking the live app, ASK FIRST.**
- **No `any`** in TS. **No direct `api.*`** in view files — go through
  repositories. **Structured `{code, message}`** errors. **Idempotency** on
  every mutating endpoint. **RLS** is the last line of defense.
- **Real-time everywhere.** Booking lists auto-refresh via Supabase Realtime,
  no pull-to-refresh. Slot grid invalidates on concurrent holds.
- **Persistent login**: cold start trusts persisted token, only 401 clears.
- **Forward-only migrations.** Apply manually in Supabase SQL Editor.
- **Deploy posture**: Render (backend) + Vercel (web) auto-deploy from `main`.
  **Never merge or push to GitHub unless the user explicitly asks** (any branch).
- **Test-driven**: Every code change updates/adds unit tests (mobile, web, backend). All tests must pass before delivery. See `.cursor/rules/test-driven.mdc`.
- **Documentation discipline**: update `docs/REMAINING_ISSUES.md` and
  `docs/PROGRESS.md` in the same commit as the code change.
- **Communication**: concise, show-don't-tell, root cause, no filler. **Bullet points only** — see `.cursor/rules/concise-output.mdc`.

If RULES.md and this file ever drift, RULES.md wins.
